main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in Summerset, Pennsylvania on July 11, 1965, reported as moving very fast and bright.
interesting points: The object was evaluated as an aircraft observation, leading to no definitive evidence to suggest otherwise,The object was reported to move from the east to the west in a short duration of 2.5 minutes,The observer noted that the object was solid and had a very bright appearance,The total duration of the sighting was approximately 30 minutes,The observer estimated the object's speed to be between 200 to 300 miles per hour.
sighted object: a bright solid object in the sky
